Are the homeless and displaced a silent issue in Singapore? 
18-year-old Harrison and Sricharan started a youth initiative, Comm.UnitySG, amidst the Covid-19 pandemic to serve the homeless and displaced in Singapore. We take a closer look at how they've been helping the residents at Jalan Kukoh, a low-income neighbourhood in Singapore comprising rental flats. 
This is their story.
